This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with brain image segmentation using deep convolutional neural networks. It could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-categories as it involves training a neural network on a large dataset. Additionally, it could be classified under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it involves the development of a new tool for brain image segmentation. Finally, it could also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category as it deals with processing and analyzing medical images.
